{"bike":{"frame_model":"ZURIGO DISC sram apex","manufacturer":"Bianchi","year":2014,"description":"Named in honor of the 1967 Cyclocross World Championships in Zurich, Switzerland, our Zurigo carries on a long tradition of delivering proven performance over varied terrains. With cyclocross racing, gravel grinding, bike commuting, credit-card touring, and back road adventure riding on the rise, now is your time to rise above on a Bianchi Zurigo. The Zurigo features a triple-butted, hydroformed aluminum frame with tubing shaped to deliver track bike acceleration and crit bike handling. A carbon fiber fork keeps the front wheel connected to the terrain while the tapered head tube provides quick and responsive steering. A Pressfit 30 bottom bracket efficiently transmits power to the rear wheel. The Zurigo\u2019s flat bottom top tube and internal down tube cable routing makes it easy to shoulder a run-up or ford a stream. 38c clearance allows for flexibility in matching tire to terrain. Avid BB-5 disc brakes stop fast in any condition. Think of the Zurigo as the \u201cSwiss Army Knife\u201d of bikes. Frame: ZURIGO Cyclocross Alu DISC BRAKE, PF30.","original_msrp":"$1,799","paint_description":["Black"],"manufacturers_url":"http://www.bianchiusa.com/bikes/off-road/zurigo-disc-sram-apex/#","rear_wheel_bsd":622,"rear_tire_narrow":"true","stock_photo_url":"https://bikebook.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/Fr/13126/csm_ZURIGO_36840eded3.jpg","stock_photo_small":"https://bikebook.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/Fr/13126/medium_csm_ZURIGO_36840eded3.jpg"},"components":[{"component_type":"fork","description":"Carbon/alloy 6061, 1.1/8\" - 1/2\", disc","cgroup":"Frame and fork"},{"component_type":"headset","description":"Fsa Orbit C-40-ACB","cgroup":"Frame and fork"},{"component_type":"shifter","description":"Sram SL APEX 10sp","cgroup":"Drivetrain and brakes"},{"component_type":"derailleur","description":"Sram APEX 10sp max 11-32","front_or_rear":"rear","cgroup":"Drivetrain and brakes"},{"compon